{
  "texts": [
    "However, the effectiveness of these models depends strongly on data quality, feature selection, and interpretability.",
    "Therefore, future financial research should focus not only on accuracy but also on explainability and robustness.",
    "For practitioners, the results show that ML and DL can enhance decision-making in areas such as credit evaluation, risk management, and portfolio optimization.",
    "Financial institutions can use these tools to process real-time data, detect anomalies, and identify early warning signals for instability or default.",
    "Nevertheless, the operational deployment of such models still faces ethical and regulatory challenges, including transparency, data privacy, and model bias."
  ]
}